# Visual regression tests — always Docker

**Default is Docker only.** Committed screenshot baselines match **Linux** (GitHub Actions + `mcr.microsoft.com/playwright`). Host macOS/Windows Playwright output is **not** acceptable for committing or “fixing” golden PNGs.

**Agents and automation:** **never** use `npm run test:visual`, `npm run test:visual:update`, or bare `npx playwright test … --update-snapshots` on the host for verification or baseline updates. **Always** use the Docker npm scripts below (including scoped specs). The only exception is a **human** doing deliberate quick local debugging — agents should not.

**Commands**

- Run full suite: `npm run test:visual:docker`
- Update snapshots (full suite): `npm run test:visual:update:docker`
- Site pages only: `npm run test:visual:site-pages:docker` / `npm run test:visual:site-pages:update:docker`

Those wrap `docker compose run --rm playwright-fast` and `playwright-update-fast` (see `README.md` and `docker-compose.yml`).

**Scoped runs** (one spec, `--grep`, etc.): still use Docker — either the dedicated `*:site-pages:*:docker` scripts in `package.json`, or override the service command so `npm ci` runs in the container, then Playwright:

```bash
docker compose run --rm playwright-fast bash -lc "npm ci --prefer-offline --no-audit --no-fund && npx playwright test tests/visual/workshop-pegboard.spec.ts"
```

Append `--update-snapshots` when refreshing baselines (or use `npm run test:visual:update:docker` for the whole suite). Use `playwright` / `playwright-update` (non-`*-fast`) only if you need the full `apt-get` toolchain path from `docker-compose.yml`.

Shell runs need Docker available (`all` / full permissions if the sandbox blocks Docker).
